WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.867 --> 00:00:03.802
Why I'm here today,
talking to you, here,

00:00:03.802 --> 00:00:06.239
in this amazing special place?

00:00:07.873 --> 00:00:11.011
It's because of a slug story.

00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:14.547 align:start size:94% position:6%
Basic slug story, you
know how those stories go?

00:00:14.547 --> 00:00:17.683
You know, I couldn't
have my pocket money

00:00:17.683 --> 00:00:18.951 line:0%
when I was a kid.

00:00:18.951 --> 00:00:21.154 line:0%
Grow up in Switzerland.

00:00:21.154 --> 00:00:22.722 line:0%
Picture this.

00:00:22.722 --> 00:00:29.562 align:start size:94% position:6% line:0%
This white peak, green field,
with nice little chalet.

00:00:29.562 --> 00:00:30.930
Can you see that?

00:00:30.930 --> 00:00:31.965
Yeah.

00:00:31.965 --> 00:00:33.232
Well it's not there.

00:00:33.232 --> 00:00:36.235
It's up north, foggy, raining,

00:00:36.235 --> 00:00:39.205 align:start size:84% position:16%
the most jobless
area in Switzerland.

00:00:39.205 --> 00:00:42.575
You usually never get
away from that place.

00:00:42.575 --> 00:00:46.178 align:start size:94% position:6%
I live in a tiny village,
it's a dead end road.

00:00:46.178 --> 00:00:48.247
There's nothing after that.

00:00:48.247 --> 00:00:52.285 align:start size:88% position:13%
You feel like you are
at the end of the world.

00:00:52.285 --> 00:00:53.353
And I grew up there.

00:00:53.353 --> 00:00:54.621
I'm from there.

00:00:56.055 --> 00:00:59.392 align:start size:94% position:6%
And I've got two brothers,
one older, one younger.

00:00:59.392 --> 00:01:02.695
And I keep going back
to my father, saying,

00:01:02.695 --> 00:01:06.065 align:start size:84% position:16%
"I need some pocket
money, give me money."

00:01:06.065 --> 00:01:08.667
He said, "no way you're
going to get money."

00:01:08.667 --> 00:01:12.839
Anyway, I annoyed him so
much, that one day he said,

00:01:13.872 --> 00:01:16.242
"okay, we make a deal."

00:01:16.242 --> 00:01:18.377 align:start size:84% position:16%
I've got the garden
full of slugs.

00:01:18.377 --> 00:01:21.815 align:start size:84% position:16%
You collect 100 slugs,
and I give you $1.

00:01:24.083 --> 00:01:25.651
Mmm.

00:01:25.651 --> 00:01:27.453
Interesting.

00:01:27.453 --> 00:01:30.756
I spend all my time in the
garden when it was raining,

00:01:30.756 --> 00:01:33.593 align:start position:0%
because those slugs were
coming out when it was raining.

00:01:33.593 --> 00:01:37.530 align:start size:84% position:16%
Collect all those
slugs, 600 I needed.

00:01:37.530 --> 00:01:40.300
And what I will
do with those $6?

00:01:41.501 --> 00:01:45.671
I will run in town, and
buy National Geographic.

00:01:45.671 --> 00:01:47.941
I was seven years old.

00:01:47.941 --> 00:01:50.777
So tonight, it's the
first presentation

00:01:50.777 --> 00:01:53.913 align:start size:88% position:13%
that I do here, in
National Geographic DC,

00:01:53.913 --> 00:01:56.682
and I'm really proud
to talk to you tonight.

00:01:56.682 --> 00:01:58.951 align:start size:84% position:16%
It's really something
deep in my heart.

00:01:58.951 --> 00:02:01.988 align:start size:84% position:16%
This is the example
that dreams come true,

00:02:01.988 --> 00:02:05.391
because I want,
as a little girl,

00:02:05.391 --> 00:02:09.595 align:start size:94% position:6%
to travel to those
weird, incredible places.

00:02:09.595 --> 00:02:12.765 align:start size:88% position:13%
So I spent my childhood
in the forest.

00:02:12.765 --> 00:02:16.102
I had this amazing
guidebook, bird book.

00:02:17.537 --> 00:02:20.907
On the front page there was
this beautiful blue bird,

00:02:20.907 --> 00:02:25.078 align:start size:97% position:3%
with a bit of red and
yellowish thing on the back.

00:02:26.712 --> 00:02:29.415
But they forgot to tell me
that it was not in Europe

00:02:29.415 --> 00:02:31.751
and not in my country.

00:02:31.751 --> 00:02:34.253 align:start size:88% position:13%
So I spent all my
childhood in the woods,

00:02:34.253 --> 00:02:35.754
looking for that bird.

00:02:35.754 --> 00:02:39.425
My parents were quite happy
I was in the woods somewhere,

00:02:39.425 --> 00:02:41.627
looking for birds.

00:02:41.627 --> 00:02:44.663 align:start size:84% position:16%
Anyway, I took my
revenge on this one.

00:02:44.663 --> 00:02:47.600 align:start size:94% position:6%
And I would like to invite
you with me tonight,

00:02:47.600 --> 00:02:50.236 align:start size:88% position:13%
we're going to be starving,
it's going to be hot,

00:02:50.236 --> 00:02:52.405 align:start size:88% position:13%
you're going to see
snakes, and crocodiles.

00:02:52.405 --> 00:02:55.675
Welcome to Dropped
Into the Wild Corner.

00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:57.844
My most recent expedition.

00:02:59.245 --> 00:03:03.149 align:start size:97% position:3%
My concern was, how we
going to feed the world today?

00:03:04.583 --> 00:03:08.054 align:start size:97% position:3%
Because I was in China, I
saw all these Chinese people,

00:03:08.054 --> 00:03:11.958 align:start size:94% position:6%
build houses like, really
high, a lot of people

00:03:13.092 --> 00:03:14.427
in the same room.

00:03:14.427 --> 00:03:16.895
And I thought, how
we going to do this?

00:03:16.895 --> 00:03:20.466 align:start size:88% position:13%
How we going to keep using
the planet that way?

00:03:20.466 --> 00:03:24.237
I was concerned about, it's
going to be somebody hungry

00:03:24.237 --> 00:03:28.107 align:start size:97% position:3%
in this world, in some ways,
in some times, coming up.

00:03:28.107 --> 00:03:30.576
How we going to do this?

00:03:30.576 --> 00:03:33.479
So, I decided to
take on a journey.

00:03:34.913 --> 00:03:37.916 align:start size:84% position:16%
I wanted to understand
how we can do this.

00:03:37.916 --> 00:03:42.088
Go back to the roots, at the
time of the gather and hunter.

00:03:43.255 --> 00:03:47.660
Yes, I will find my own
food, on my own terms,

00:03:47.660 --> 00:03:50.729
following the Aboriginal people,
that have been doing this

00:03:50.729 --> 00:03:51.864
for 60,000 years.

00:03:51.864 --> 00:03:52.699
So.

00:03:53.800 --> 00:03:54.968
But, as usual.

00:03:57.870 --> 00:04:00.206 align:start size:88% position:13%
Expeditions really start
when things go wrong.

00:04:00.206 --> 00:04:03.642 align:start size:97% position:3%
And start to be really going
wrong at the first minute

00:04:03.642 --> 00:04:05.611
of the expedition.

00:04:05.611 --> 00:04:10.148 align:start size:97% position:3%
So, I learned in a little
town, on the northwest corner

00:04:10.148 --> 00:04:12.819
of Australia, called Kununurra.

00:04:14.053 --> 00:04:15.721
Word like that long.

00:04:15.721 --> 00:04:19.292 align:start size:88% position:13%
It's a weird town,
where you've got cowboy,

00:04:19.292 --> 00:04:23.463
Aboriginal people, mining
people, all mixed together.

00:04:25.931 --> 00:04:29.268 align:start size:84% position:16%
Arrive there with a
little airplane, land,

00:04:29.268 --> 00:04:35.441
and I open my phone, my dear
friend supposed to be there,

00:04:35.441 --> 00:04:40.112
helping me for one month to go
and check all my techniques,

00:04:40.112 --> 00:04:41.614
surviving techniques
that I've been learning

00:04:41.614 --> 00:04:43.349
over the years.

00:04:43.349 --> 00:04:47.620 align:start size:94% position:6%
Included really technical
fishing techniques.

00:04:47.620 --> 00:04:50.089 align:start size:94% position:6%
And I received this lovely
text, it was saying,

00:04:50.089 --> 00:04:52.825
"Sorry darling,
I can't make it."

00:04:54.060 --> 00:04:56.095
I was like, "What?!"

00:04:56.095 --> 00:04:59.699 align:start size:88% position:13%
We've been planning
this for a year, what?!

00:05:01.534 --> 00:05:05.238
And I tried to call
him like 55 times,

00:05:05.238 --> 00:05:07.439
never answered the phone.

00:05:07.439 --> 00:05:09.441
And I called my team
back in Switzerland

00:05:09.441 --> 00:05:13.045 align:start size:84% position:16%
and I said, hey guys,
how we going to do this?

00:05:13.045 --> 00:05:14.947 align:start size:84% position:16%
And my assistant was
getting agitated.

00:05:14.947 --> 00:05:19.118
Sarah, my god, you have to
leave in four weeks time,

00:05:20.319 --> 00:05:22.188
how we going to do this?

00:05:22.188 --> 00:05:23.555
I said, you know darling,

00:05:23.555 --> 00:05:25.691 align:start size:84% position:16%
when things get
agitated like that,

00:05:25.691 --> 00:05:27.993
there's only one option.

00:05:27.993 --> 00:05:30.462
I'm going to drink coffee.

00:05:30.462 --> 00:05:34.133
You know, in nature,
when there is a danger,

00:05:35.668 --> 00:05:38.704 align:start size:84% position:16%
and there is
something so intense,

00:05:38.704 --> 00:05:41.040
animals just stop and froze.

00:05:41.040 --> 00:05:43.542 align:start size:88% position:13%
I'm just going to stop and
froze and drink coffee

00:05:43.542 --> 00:05:45.745 align:start size:81% position:19%
until I see a sign
in front of me.

00:05:45.745 --> 00:05:47.279
That's it.

00:05:47.279 --> 00:05:52.184 align:start size:97% position:3%
And I can hear my assistant,
"you are crazy darling."

00:05:52.184 --> 00:05:53.452
I did that.

00:05:53.452 --> 00:05:56.088
Stop in a coffee shop,
drink for five hours.

00:05:56.088 --> 00:05:58.924
The night went down,
I took my little car,

00:05:58.924 --> 00:06:02.728 align:start size:94% position:6%
went to find my
accommodation that night.

00:06:02.728 --> 00:06:05.631
I booked a room in the farm,

00:06:05.631 --> 00:06:10.269 align:start size:97% position:3%
and this lady, received
me, she was waiting for me,

00:06:10.269 --> 00:06:14.506
and she just walked out of
the door of the property.

00:06:14.506 --> 00:06:16.843
She had a designer dress on.

00:06:18.044 --> 00:06:22.114
Pink dress, beautiful,
hair done, makeup on.

00:06:22.114 --> 00:06:24.083
I was like, what?!

00:06:24.083 --> 00:06:27.853 align:start size:97% position:3%
I'm in the remotest location
in the bush in Australia,

00:06:27.853 --> 00:06:31.156
and she's wearing
this kind of thing?

00:06:31.156 --> 00:06:33.626
I thought, this woman
never going to help me,

00:06:33.626 --> 00:06:34.960
not this one.

00:06:34.960 --> 00:06:36.428
Went to bed.

00:06:36.428 --> 00:06:38.263 align:start size:88% position:13%
Anyway, the next morning
she knock on my door,

00:06:38.263 --> 00:06:41.701
and she say, "Sarah, do you
want to have coffee with me?"

00:06:41.701 --> 00:06:43.535
Say, "lovely, yeah."

00:06:43.535 --> 00:06:44.370
Why not?

00:06:45.437 --> 00:06:47.606 align:start size:84% position:16%
Anyway, we had
coffee, and she said,

00:06:47.606 --> 00:06:50.709
"what brings you here, darling?"

00:06:50.709 --> 00:06:53.212
Say, "well, I'm coming to walk."

00:06:55.581 --> 00:06:58.951
I try not to deliver too many
information at the same time,

00:06:58.951 --> 00:07:01.553 align:start size:97% position:3%
because usually I get
arrested before I do anything.

00:07:01.553 --> 00:07:05.591
So, I learned my lesson in
China when I get arrested

00:07:05.591 --> 00:07:09.194 align:start size:94% position:6%
by Special Forces, I
learned my lesson in Laos

00:07:09.194 --> 00:07:12.397
when the drug dealer arrest me,

00:07:12.397 --> 00:07:17.002
I learned my lesson in
Mongolia when Mongol man

00:07:17.002 --> 00:07:21.174 align:start size:97% position:3%
ran through my camp every
night tried to steal my stuff.

00:07:22.341 --> 00:07:25.678 align:start size:84% position:16%
So, yeah, I was hoping
to do some walking.

00:07:27.179 --> 00:07:29.615
And she said, she
jumped on her seat,

00:07:29.615 --> 00:07:31.950 align:start size:84% position:16%
really literally
jumped, and she said,

00:07:31.950 --> 00:07:34.953
well, I just come
back from Europe.

00:07:34.953 --> 00:07:37.723
I did the Camino, in Europe.

00:07:37.723 --> 00:07:39.825
I was like, what?!

00:07:39.825 --> 00:07:41.894
She was a walker.

00:07:41.894 --> 00:07:44.296
Anyway, she said, you
want some brownie?

00:07:44.296 --> 00:07:46.165
I said, "of course I
want some brownie."

00:07:46.165 --> 00:07:49.601 align:start size:94% position:6%
She got some fresh brownie
coming from the oven,

00:07:49.601 --> 00:07:52.104
I said, "yes, let's
have some brownie."

00:07:52.104 --> 00:07:55.608 align:start size:88% position:13%
We start chatting, like
two women can chat.

00:07:55.608 --> 00:07:57.509 align:start size:84% position:16%
And she said, 
"don't worry, wait."

00:07:57.509 --> 00:07:59.978
She took the phone, make
like five phone calls.

00:07:59.978 --> 00:08:02.882 align:start position:0%
She said, "okay, you've got a
meeting tomorrow with this one,"

00:08:02.882 --> 00:08:05.150 align:start size:84% position:16%
"then a coffee at
four with this one,"

00:08:05.150 --> 00:08:07.286
"dinner with this one."

00:08:07.286 --> 00:08:08.788
I said who is this woman?

00:08:08.788 --> 00:08:11.090
You will see, go, I don't
have time to come with you,

00:08:11.090 --> 00:08:12.324 size:81% position:41%
but you'll manage.

00:08:12.324 --> 00:08:16.495
Anyway, in a weeks time,
I made this networking

00:08:16.495 --> 00:08:19.498
of powerful women in this town.

00:08:19.498 --> 00:08:21.967
The lawyer of the town,
the doctor of the town,

00:08:21.967 --> 00:08:24.704
I had all of them
under my wings.

00:08:26.138 --> 00:08:30.309
And they pushed me, and helped
me to rebuild my expedition.

00:08:30.309 --> 00:08:32.077 align:start size:84% position:16%
Reroute completely
my expedition,

00:08:32.077 --> 00:08:33.846
restart from scratch.

00:08:35.581 --> 00:08:38.984
And four weeks later,
I was ready to go.

00:08:38.984 --> 00:08:42.054
But everybody, that
I was talking to,

00:08:42.054 --> 00:08:44.690 align:start size:97% position:3%
having the same
conversation over and over,

00:08:44.690 --> 00:08:47.993 align:start size:84% position:16%
was saying to me,
it's a drought year.

00:08:47.993 --> 00:08:50.529
There is not enough
water in the bush,

00:08:50.529 --> 00:08:52.231
you will not be able to survive.

00:08:52.231 --> 00:08:54.700
Everybody was saying that.

00:08:54.700 --> 00:08:56.569
And you know, when people
are always got this opinion

00:08:56.569 --> 00:08:58.069
about my expedition.

00:08:58.069 --> 00:08:59.671
They look at me, they judge me,

00:08:59.671 --> 00:09:00.972
they look at me and they say,

00:09:00.972 --> 00:09:02.441
"What this blondie-thing hair,

00:09:02.441 --> 00:09:05.244 align:start size:81% position:19%
"she's not good
for these things."

00:09:06.412 --> 00:09:09.614
Anyway, I thought,
maybe this time,

00:09:09.614 --> 00:09:12.584
I better listen a little bit.

00:09:12.584 --> 00:09:14.319
And I decided to do a test.

00:09:14.319 --> 00:09:16.389
And before, I wanted to spend

00:09:16.389 --> 00:09:18.323 align:start size:81% position:19%
some time with
Aboriginal people.

00:09:18.323 --> 00:09:20.726
That's how I met Juju.

00:09:20.726 --> 00:09:24.363 align:start size:97% position:3%
In a center, it's a
full-blood Aboriginal woman.

00:09:24.363 --> 00:09:27.700 align:start size:84% position:16%
Really important woman
in her community.

00:09:29.135 --> 00:09:32.137
And, the young people around
her is the new generation.

00:09:32.137 --> 00:09:34.707
They're the kids of her sister.

00:09:38.210 --> 00:09:42.180
So, you can see the pure
blood, it's really rare

00:09:42.180 --> 00:09:45.951
to find some pure-blood
Aboriginal these days.

00:09:45.951 --> 00:09:49.622
And we went on a tour
together, in the bush.

00:09:50.522 --> 00:09:52.124
We spent some time in the bush,

00:09:52.124 --> 00:09:55.594
and she will give
me some tricks.

00:09:55.594 --> 00:09:58.931
But she will not give
me all the tricks.

00:10:00.299 --> 00:10:02.401
She didn't know that I know.

00:10:02.401 --> 00:10:04.937
She didn't know that I have
been preparing these things

00:10:04.937 --> 00:10:05.972
for 20 years.

00:10:07.406 --> 00:10:10.309 align:start size:94% position:6%
So she will give me the
tricks, but not all of it.

00:10:10.309 --> 00:10:13.345 align:start size:88% position:13%
She will give me the
wrong plant to look for.

00:10:13.345 --> 00:10:17.349
Not the good ripe ones, she
will give me the young one,

00:10:17.349 --> 00:10:20.419 align:start size:84% position:16%
where there was
nothing to eat there.

00:10:20.419 --> 00:10:24.490
And I was wondering, the
more I spent time with her,

00:10:24.490 --> 00:10:26.325
what's going on here?

00:10:26.325 --> 00:10:29.227
Why she doesn't give
me the full trick?

00:10:29.227 --> 00:10:33.899
Is it because she feel
like I don't own my path

00:10:33.899 --> 00:10:35.400
through her land?

00:10:35.400 --> 00:10:38.236 align:start size:94% position:6%
Or it is because she
don't want me to get hurt

00:10:38.236 --> 00:10:39.938
and go back home?

00:10:39.938 --> 00:10:42.908
I didn't know what
she was thinking.

00:10:42.908 --> 00:10:45.511 align:start size:97% position:3%
I didn't know what everybody
was thinking, really.

00:10:45.511 --> 00:10:48.180
I decided to do a test.

00:10:48.180 --> 00:10:49.648
And I just did that.

00:10:49.648 --> 00:10:53.285 align:start size:97% position:3%
I went in the bush, get
dropped with a little plane,

00:10:53.285 --> 00:10:55.987
walked for seven days,
and discovered exactly

00:10:55.987 --> 00:10:57.489
what they were talking about.

00:10:57.489 --> 00:10:59.525
There was not enough food there.

00:10:59.525 --> 00:11:01.727
They were right, actually.

00:11:01.727 --> 00:11:05.197 align:start size:84% position:16%
So, I decided to take
a Plan B with me,

00:11:05.197 --> 00:11:09.134
I decided to take 150
grams of flour per day

00:11:09.134 --> 00:11:10.469
as a Plan B.

00:11:10.469 --> 00:11:12.738
If things go wrong.

00:11:12.738 --> 00:11:15.007
So I looked like that.

00:11:15.007 --> 00:11:17.609
It's a little flat bread,

00:11:17.609 --> 00:11:21.047
and I wonder today if
it was a good idea.

00:11:21.047 --> 00:11:24.183
Because you know, when
you've got, in your pack,

00:11:24.183 --> 00:11:28.354 align:start position:0%
food, you so starving but
you're not allowed to touch it.

00:11:31.890 --> 00:11:34.292
It's like having the
fridge full of food,

00:11:34.292 --> 00:11:35.795
and you in a diet.

00:11:37.296 --> 00:11:38.564
Can't touch it.

00:11:40.399 --> 00:11:41.734
It was horrible.

00:11:42.901 --> 00:11:45.705
But I desired to
do this that way.

00:11:47.138 --> 00:11:49.374 align:start size:97% position:3%
So let's go, we're going to get
dropped with a helicopter

00:11:49.374 --> 00:11:51.777
northwest of Australia.

00:11:51.777 --> 00:11:55.614 align:start size:84% position:16%
Precisely there,
there's nobody there.

00:11:55.614 --> 00:11:58.884
It's empty land, no
human, it's for me.

00:12:00.986 --> 00:12:03.489
So, get dropped there
with the helicopter,

00:12:03.489 --> 00:12:06.658
the pilot said to me, "Are
you sure you want to get

00:12:06.658 --> 00:12:09.161 align:start size:84% position:16%
"dropped here?
There's nothing here."

00:12:09.161 --> 00:12:11.930
I said this is exactly where
I want to get dropped, here.

00:12:11.930 --> 00:12:14.100
And he said, "okay, good luck."

00:12:14.100 --> 00:12:15.434
And he fly away.

00:12:16.768 --> 00:12:20.106
And I can hear the
