You are on the menu.

00:18:09.354 --> 00:18:10.588
So, you don't want that.

00:18:10.588 --> 00:18:13.124
So nobody never told me
what to do, actually,

00:18:13.124 --> 00:18:15.260
to know if it's the
crocodile there.

00:18:15.260 --> 00:18:18.162
So I discovered the call
of the crocodile that day.

00:18:18.162 --> 00:18:19.431
And that was a good day for me,

00:18:19.431 --> 00:18:22.200 align:start size:84% position:16%
because the day
coming on from there,

00:18:22.200 --> 00:18:25.236
I would actually smash my
shirt, put a bit of water

00:18:25.236 --> 00:18:26.905
on the bottom, and I
would actually discover

00:18:26.905 --> 00:18:29.908 align:start size:84% position:16%
if there was crocodile
there or not.

00:18:31.309 --> 00:18:33.511
So when you're going
to do those things,

00:18:33.511 --> 00:18:36.415
the only thing you have to know,

00:18:36.415 --> 00:18:37.648
you have to be able

00:18:37.648 --> 00:18:40.986
to read the landscape
like a treasure map.

00:18:42.254 --> 00:18:45.457
I would find, sometimes,
some water just because

00:18:45.457 --> 00:18:48.794
I found a little bird
on a type of tree.

00:18:50.595 --> 00:18:53.532
Because I know all those birds.

00:18:53.532 --> 00:18:56.802
The little red bird,
the diamond finch,

00:18:58.003 --> 00:19:01.272
I know they can fly five
kilometers around only.

